Package: my-hello-module
Architecture: any
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, dkms (>= 2.2.0.3), linux-image-generic
Description: Sample kernel module packaged via APT with DKMS
 This package demonstrates how to bundle a Linux kernel module in a Debian
 package using DKMS (Dynamic Kernel Module Support). When installed, it
 registers the module with DKMS so it gets automatically rebuilt for new
 kernels. The module creates /proc/myhello with a greeting message.